(735, 'School Teachers’ Review Body', 'Department for Education', 'The School Teachers’ Review Body was established to report to the Prime Minister and to the Secretary of State for Education on the statutory pay and conditions of school teachers in England and Wales. Its recommendations cover pay and conditions for school teachers.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/school-teachers-review-body', 'accidentally published', '935,000', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(736, 'Science Advisory Committee on the Medical Implications of Less-Lethal Weapons', 'Ministry of Defence', 'To provide advice on the biophysical, biomechanical, pathological and clinical aspects of generic classes of less-lethal weapon systems.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/science-advisory-committee-on-the-medical-implications-of-less-lethal-weapons', 'hacked', '200 stores', 'Ransomware', 1),
(737, 'Science Advisory Council', 'Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs', 'The SAC challenges and supports the Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser (CSA) in independently assuring and challenging the evidence underpinning Defra policies and ensuring that the evidence programme meets Defra’s needs.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/science-advisory-council', 'lost / stolen computer', '4,243,434', 'Logic bombs', 1),
(738, 'Science and Technology Facilities Council', 'Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy', 'STFC supports university-based research, innovation and skills development in astronomy, particle physics, nuclear physics, and space science by granting access to large-scale scientific facilities.', 'http://www.stfc.ac.uk/', 'hacked', '2,434,899', 'Worms', 1),
(739, 'Science Museum Group', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'To care for, preserve and add to the objects in the collections, to ensure that objects are exhibited to the public and to promote the public’s enjoyment and understanding of science and technology.', 'http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/about_us/smg.aspx', 'lost / stolen media', '17,000,000', 'Droppers', 1),
(740, 'Sea Fish Industry Authority', 'Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs', 'Supports all sectors of the seafood industry for a sustainable, profitable future and aims to support and improve the environmental sustainability, efficiency and cost-effectiveness of the industry, as well as promoting sustainably-sourced seafood. Seafish is funded by a levy on the first sale of seafood landed and imported in the UK.', 'http://www.seafish.org/', 'hacked', '20,000,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(741, 'Security Industry Authority', 'Home Office', 'The Security Industry Authority (SIA) is the organisation responsible for regulating the private security industry. They are an independent body reporting to the Home Secretary, under the terms of the Private Security Industry Act 2001.', 'http://sia.homeoffice.gov.uk/Pages/home.aspx', 'hacked', '70,000,000', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(742, 'Security Vetting Appeals Panel', 'Cabinet Office', 'To hear appeals against the refusal or withdrawal of security clearance and to make recommendations to the appropriate head of department.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/security-vetting-appeals-panel', 'hacked', '28,722,877', 'File infectors', 1),
(743, 'Senior Salaries Review Body', 'Cabinet Office', 'The Review Body on Senior Salaries provides independent advice to the Prime Minister, the Lord Chancellor and the Secretary of State for Defence on the remuneration of holders of judicial office, senior civil servants, senior officers of the armed forces and other such public appointments as may from time to time be specified.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/review-body-on-senior-salaries', 'hacked', 'unknown', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(744, 'Sentencing Council for England and Wales', 'Ministry of Justice', 'The Sentencing Council for England and Wales promotes greater consistency in sentencing, whilst maintaining the independence of the judiciary. The Council produces guidelines on sentencing for the judiciary and aims to increase public understanding of sentencing.', 'http://www.sentencingcouncil.org.uk/', 'hacked', '6,300,000', 'File infectors', 1),
(745, 'Serious Fraud Office', 'Serious Fraud Office', 'The Serious Fraud Office is an independent government department, operating under the superintendence of the Attorney General.  Its purpose is to protect society by investigating and, if appropriate, prosecuting those who commit serious or complex fraud, bribery and corruption and pursuing them and others for the proceeds of their crime.  It operates in line with its statutory purpose and policies.  Its Director is David Green CB QC.', 'http://www.sfo.gov.uk/', 'hacked', '260,000', 'System or boot-record infectors', 1),
(746, 'Single Source Regulations Office (SSRO)', 'Ministry of Defence', 'The SSRO regulates the UK government’s procurement of ‘single source’, or non-competitive, military goods, works and services. It is the independent statutory regulator of single source defence procurement, issuing statutory guidance, assessing compliance and determining how the regime applies to individual contracts. Our principal statutory aims are to ensure that good value for money is obtained for the UK taxpayer in expenditure on qualifying defence contracts, and that single source suppliers are paid a fair and reasonable price under those contracts.', 'https://www.gov.uk/ssro', 'accidentally published', '170,000', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(747, 'Sir John Soane''s Museum', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'This is the House, Museum and Collections of the architect Sir John Soane, who died in 1837. The Collections comprise works of art, paintings, books, manuscripts and architectural models and drawings.', 'http://www.soane.org/', 'inside job', '89,000', 'Ransomware', 1),
(748, 'Skills Funding Agency', 'Department for Education', 'The Skills Funding Agency funds and promotes adult further education and skills training in England (excluding higher education).', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/skills-funding-agency (until 31 March 2017)\n\nwww.gov.uk/efsa (after 1 April 2017)', 'lost / stolen media', '12,500,000', 'Logic bombs', 1),
(749, 'Social Mobility Commission', 'Department for Education', 'The Social Mobility Commission (SMC) monitors the progress towards improving social mobility in the UK, and promotes social mobility in England. It was previously called the Social Mobility and Child Poverty Commission until 2016 when the legislative base was amended in the Welfare Reform and Work Act 2016.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/social-mobility-commission', 'hacked', '28,000,000', 'Worms', 1),
(750, 'Social Science Research Committee, The', 'Food Standards Agency', 'Provides advice to the Food Standards Agency about how it gathers and uses social science evidence.', 'http://ssrc.food.gov.uk/', 'hacked', '26,151,608', 'Droppers', 1),
(751, 'Social Security Advisory Committee', 'Department for Work and Pensions', 'Provides advice to the Secretary of State on proposals for the amendment of secondary legislation and on general social security matters.', 'http://gov.uk/SSAC', 'hacked', '94,000,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(752, 'Sport England', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'Sport England wants everyone in England regardless of age, background or level of ability to feel able to engage in sport and physical acitivity', 'http://www.sportengland.org/', 'lost / stolen computer', '4,901,432', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(753, 'Sports Grounds Safety Authority', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'To create the conditions for safe and enjoyable experiences for people at all sports grounds, not only in England and Wales, but around the world and to provide trusted advice and guidance, and use our experience and commitment to drive continuous improvement.', 'http://www.safetyatsportsgrounds.org.uk/', 'lost / stolen media', '398,000', 'File infectors', 1),
(754, 'Standards and Testing Agency', 'Department for Education', 'The Standards and Testing Agency (STA), an executive agency of the Department for Education, is responsible for the development and delivery of all statutory assessments from early years to the end of Key Stage 2, delivering the professional skills tests for prospective teachers and putting in place the logistics arrangements for completed general qualification scripts.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/standards-and-testing-agency', 'hacked', '8 locations', 'System or boot-record infectors', 1),
(755, 'Student Loans Company', 'Department for Education', 'The Student Loans Company (SLC)  is a non-profit making government-owned organisation set up to provide loans and grants to students in universities and colleges in the UK.', 'http://www.slc.co.uk/', 'hacked', '65,469,298', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(756, 'Tate', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'To increase the public’s understanding and enjoyment of British art from the 16th century to the present day and of international modern and contemporary art.', 'http://www.tate.org.uk/', 'hacked', 'unknown', 'Ransomware', 1),
(757, 'Technical Advisory Board', 'Home Office', 'To advise the Home Secretary on whether obligations imposed on communications service providers under the terms of the Regulation of Investigatory Powers Act 2000 (RIPA) and Investigatory Powers Act 2016 (IPA) are reasonable.', 'http://www.gov.uk/tab', 'hacked', '250,000', 'Logic bombs', 1);
