(758, 'The Pensions Ombudsman', 'Department for Work and Pensions', 'To investigate and decide on complaints and disputes concerning occupational and personal pension schemes. The Ombudsman is completely independent and acts as an impartial adjudicator.', 'http://www.pensions-ombudsman.org.uk/', 'poor security', 'unknown', 'Worms', 1),
(759, 'The Pensions Regulator', 'Department for Work and Pensions', 'To protect the benefits of members of occupational pension schemes , to protect the benefits of members of personal pension schemes (where there is a direct payment arrangement), to promote, and to improve understanding of the good administration of work-based pension schemes, to reduce the risk of situations arising which may lead to compensation being payable from the Pension Protection Fund (PPF), to maximise employer compliance with employer duties and the employment safeguards introduced by the Pensions Act 2008, to minimise any adverse impact on the sustainable growth of an employer (in relation to the exercise of the regulator’s functions under Part 3 of the Pensions Act 2004 only). Our new objective on sustainable growth came into force on 14 July 2014.', 'http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/', 'accidentally published', '50,000', 'Droppers', 1),
(760, 'Theatres Trust, The', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'The Trust was established to promote the protection of theatres for the benefit of the nation. It is also a statutory consultee in the Planning system. Its remit covers England, Scotland and Wales.', 'http://www.theatrestrust.org.uk/', 'inside job', '392,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(761, 'Traffic Commissioners\nfor Great Britain', 'Department for Transport', 'The seven Traffic Commissioners are appointed by the Secretary of State for Transport and have responsibility for: the licensing of the operators of heavy goods vehicles (HGVs) and of buses and coaches; the registration of local bus services and taking action against drivers of HGVs and (PSVs) public service vehicles in certain circumstances.', 'www.gov.uk/traffic-commissioners', '', '', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(762, 'Transport Focus', 'Department for Transport', 'Transport Focus (officially the Passengers’ Council) is the independent transport user watchdog, whose mission is to get the best deal for passengers and, since 30 March 2015, road users. Transport Focus represents rail passengers in England, Scotland and Wales, bus and tram passengers in England (outside London) passengers on scheduled domestic coach services, and users of the strategic road network in England.', 'www.transportfocus.org.uk', 'lost / stolen media', '72,000', 'File infectors', 1),
(763, 'Treasure Valuation Committee', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'To recommend to the Secretary of State valuations for the items brought before it and to provide advice to the Secretary of State in cases where there is grounds for dispute (Treasure Act 1996 Code of Practice, para. 65-85).', 'http://finds.org.uk/treasure', 'lost / stolen computer', '26,500,000', 'System or boot-record infectors', 1),
(764, 'Tribunal Procedure Committee', 'Ministry of Justice', 'The Tribunal Procedure Committee was created by paragraph 22 of the Tribunals, Courts and Enforcement Act 2007 to make rules governing the practice and procedure in the First–tier Tribunal and Upper Tribunal.', 'http://www.justice.gov.uk/about/tribunal-procedure-committee', 'inside job', '260,000', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(765, 'Trinity House', 'Department for Transport', 'Trinity House has powers and responsibilities in connection with the provision, maintenance, alteration, inspection and control of lighthouses, buoys and beacons for England and Wales,  the Channel Islands, and at Gibraltar. Trinity House carries out a number of Maritime Charitable activities which are outside of its statutory functions.', 'www.trinityhouse.co.uk', 'accidentally published', '123,461', 'Ransomware', 1),
(766, 'UK Anti Doping', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'The UK’s National Anti-Doping Organisation, as defined in the World Anti-Doping Code.  UK Anti-Doping protects the right of athletes to compete in doping-free sport.', 'http://www.ukad.org.uk/', 'poor security', '50,000', 'Logic bombs', 1),
(767, 'UK Atomic Energy Authority', 'Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy', 'UKAEA researches fusion energy and related technologies, with the aim of positioning the UK as a leader in sustainable nuclear energy.', 'www.gov.uk/ukaea', 'hacked', '57,000,000', 'Worms', 1),
(768, 'UK Debt Management Office', 'Her Majesty''s Treasury', 'The DMO''s main role is to carry out the Government''s debt management policy of minimising financing costs over the long term, taking account of risk, and to minimise the cost of offsetting the Government''s net cash flows over time, while operating in a risk appetite approved by Ministers in both cases.', 'http://www.dmo.gov.uk/', 'hacked', 'unknown', 'Droppers', 1),
(769, 'UK Hydrographic Office', 'Ministry of Defence', 'To provide navigation charts and other hydrographic products and services to Defence, UK and other Governments, and for commercial shipping.', 'http://www.ukho.gov.uk/', 'hacked', '2,000,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(770, 'UK Space Agency', 'Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy', 'UKSA is responsible for all strategic decisions on the UK civil space programme and provides a clear, single voice for UK space ambitions.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-space-agency', 'hacked', '4,500,000', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(771, 'UK Statistics Authority', 'UK Statistics Authority', 'The Authority’s functions relate to its statutory areas of responsibility: oversight of the UK official statistics system, which includes around 30 central government departments and the devolved administrations, and the promotion, safeguarding and monitoring of quality, comprehensiveness and good practice in relation to all official statistics, wherever produced; production of a Code of Practice for Statistics and assessment of official statistics against the code; and governance of the Office for National Statistics (ONS) the UK’s National Statistical Institute and the largest producer of official statistics.', 'http://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/', 'lost / stolen media', '3,000,000', 'File infectors', 1),
(772, 'UK Supreme Court', 'UK Supreme Court', 'The Court hears appeals on arguable points of law of the greatest public importance, for the whole of the United Kingdom in civil cases, and for England, Wales and Northern Ireland in criminal cases. Additionally, it hears cases on devolution matters under the Scotland Act 1998, the Northern Ireland Act 1988 and the Government of Wales Act 2006, this includes issues about whether the devolved executive and legislative authorities in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have acted or propose to act within their powers or have failed to comply with any other duty imposed on them.', 'http://www.supremecourt.gov.uk/', 'lost / stolen media', '84,000', 'System or boot-record infectors', 1),
(773, 'United Kingdom Sports Council', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'UK Sport is responsible for working in partnership with the home country sports councils and other agencies to lead the UK to world class success in Olympic and Paralympic sports and secure hosting sporting events in the UK.', 'http://www.uksport.gov.uk/', 'lost / stolen media', '1,700,000', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(774, 'Valuation Office Agency', 'Her Majesty''s Revenue and Customs', 'The Valuation Office Agency is responsible for providing valuations and property advice to support taxation and benefits', 'http://www.voa.gov.uk/', 'lost / stolen media', '25,000,000', 'Ransomware', 1),
(775, 'Valuation Tribunal for England', 'Department for Communities and Local Government', 'To determine appeals concerning business rates and council tax (valuation, liability and reduction schemes).', 'http://www.valuationtribunal.gov.uk/WhoWeAre/Valuation_Tribunal_for_England.aspx', 'hacked', '150,000,000', 'Logic bombs', 1),
(776, 'Valuation Tribunal Service', 'Department for Communities and Local Government', 'To provide staff, accommodation and other support (including general advice about procedure in relation to proceedings before tribunals) to the Valuation Tribunal for England.', 'http://www.valuationtribunal.gov.uk/', 'poor security', '60,000,000', 'Worms', 1),
(777, 'Vehicle Certification Agency', 'Department for Transport', 'The Vehicle Certification Agency (VCA) is an Executive Agency of the Department for Transport (DfT). The VCA delivers its responsibilities to the Secretary of State for Transport as the UK Type Approval Authority for new on and off-road vehicles, systems and components.', 'www.dft.gov.uk/vca', 'hacked', '160,000', 'Droppers', 1),
(778, 'Veterans Advisory and Pensions Committees', 'Ministry of Defence', 'Veterans Advisory and Pensions Committees (VAPC) play a central role in promoting the interests and welfare of veterans by: raising awareness of schemes administered by DBS Veterans UK; welfare pathways; advising and signposting veterans; and providing a consultative body able to engage with the MOD.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterans-advisory-and-pensions-committees-x13', 'hacked', '80,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(779, 'Veterinary Medicines Directorate', 'Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs', 'To protect public health, animal health and the environment and to promote animal welfare by assuring the safety, quality and efficacy of veterinary medicines.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate', 'hacked', '63,000', 'Macro viruses', 1),
(780, 'Veterinary Products Committee', 'Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs', 'Advises the Secretary of State on veterinary medicines, animal feed additives and promotes the collection of information relating to suspected adverse reactions to veterinary medicines. It considers representations by market authorisation holders/applicants in relation to granting, refusal or revocation of a marketing authorisation or animal test certificate.', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-products-committee', 'hacked', '300,000', 'File infectors', 1),
(781, 'Victoria and Albert Museum', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'As the world’s leading museum of art and design, the V&A enriches people’s lives by promoting the practice of design and increasing knowledge, understanding and enjoyment of the designed world.', 'http://www.vam.ac.uk/', 'lost / stolen computer', '2,100,000', 'System or boot-record infectors', 1),
(782, 'VisitBritain', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'VisitBritain is the national tourism agency responsible for marketing Britain worldwide and developing Britain''s visitor economy. Working with partners in the  UK and Overseas to ensure Britain is marketed in an inspirational and relevant way around the world.', 'http://www.visitbritain.org', 'lost / stolen media', '2,200,000', 'Polymorphic viruses', 1),
(783, 'VisitEngland', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'VisitEngland is the national tourist board for England.  Responsible for marketing England to domestic markets and for improving England''s tourism product.', 'http://www.visitengland.com/', 'hacked', '73,000', 'Ransomware', 1),
(784, 'Wallace Collection', 'Department for Culture, Media and Sport', 'To maintain and display the collection bequeathed to the nation by Lady Wallace and interpret for the public.', 'http://www.wallacecollection.org/', 'hacked', '51 locations', 'Logic bombs', 1),
(785, 'Westminster Foundation for Democracy, The', 'Foreign and Commonwealth Office', 'The Westminster Foundation for Democracy''s work focuses on strengthening parliaments and political parties in Africa, Asia, Eastern Europe and the Middle East.', 'http://www.wfd.org/', 'poor security', '30,000', 'Worms', 1),
(786, 'Wilton Park', 'Foreign and Commonwealth Office', 'To support delivery of HMG''s foreign policy priorities through organisation of circa 50 conferences a year.', 'https://www.wiltonpark.org.uk/', 'hacked', '780,000', 'Droppers', 1),
(787, 'Youth Justice Board for England and Wales', 'Ministry of Justice', 'The Youth Justice Board oversees the youth justice system in England and Wales, working to prevent offending and reoffending by children and young people under the age of 18 and ensuring that custody for them is safe, secure, and addresses the causes of their offending behaviour.', 'http://www.justice.gov.uk/about/yjb', 'hacked', '21,500,000', 'Spyware', 1),
(788, '21st Century Oncology', 'healthcare', 'To advise Health Ministers with respect to the grant, renewal, suspension, revocation and variation of certificates and generally in connection with the system of prior authorisation required by Article 5(a) of Council Directive 76/579/Euratom. This has been superseded by the Basic Safety Standard Directive for radiation protection 059/2013 but not yet implemented into UK law.', ' https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/930124877/?refId=d3493ec8-privateid.37f8-4218-92b2-4656b383a955&trk=eml-jymbii-organic-job-card&midToken=serverattack/AQHBnYxQHAJchw&trkEmail=eml-jobs_jymbii_digest-null-4-null-null-9xzoen~joem4ler~uj-null-jobs~view&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_jobs_jymbii_digest%3BCxmcCwrxR62ABhqSrl2dYA%3D%3D', 'hacked', '1,500,000', 'Macro viruses', 1),
